						<summary>

						<p>On the east wall of the <hi rend="italic">Kalyāṇa maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the Parāśarēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>[Rājarāja]</p>						

						<p>This inscription belongs to the reign of Rājarāja III (Vide No. 299 above and No. 304 below).</p>						

						<p>This records the setting up of the image of Śrīkaraṇappiḷḷaiyār by the temple accountant Perumuḷaiyūruḍaiyāṉ Tiruchchiṟṟambalamuḍaiyāṉ Śiṅga-ppiḷḷai <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Vāgīśa-pperumāḷ.<note n="128-2">Incomplete. Published in T.T.D. Inscriptions, Vol. 1, No. 39.</note></p>						

						</summary>
